history.content: CS 189 is usually safe to phase 2. In my experience a lot of people drop because they realize they don't meet the math prerequisites.

children.subject: @Brian Chu - following up on your answer, and related to @1263, how strict are the pre-reqs in the class? Will not having taken them (especially Math 53) affect one's performance in 189?
@Brian Chu you were really wrong this time about 189. I listened and waited till phase II, and now I probably won't get in :(

history.content: I read @1228 which mentioned something about the popularity of CS 189, but since C106A and 149 are relatively small classes (around 30 and 40 students respectively), I was wondering whether I should phase 1 both of those? Is it feasible to leave CS 189 to phase 2? What about leaving one of C106A or 149 to phase 2, and doing 189 in phase 1?
